webpackJsonp([0x738c4256382f0800],{"./node_modules/json-loader/index.js!./.cache/json/mathematics-multiplying-fractions.json":function(s,n){s.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<h2>Multiplying Fractions</h2>\n<p>A fraction is generally used to represent a number which is a ratio of two numbers.</p>\n<p>Consider the fraction <span class="fraction"><sup>4</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span>, here 4 is called the numerator and 5 is called the denominator. </p>\n<p>Here are the steps to multiply two fractions</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Multiply the numerator and denominator of the fractions</li>\n<li>If possible, simplify the resultant fraction</li>\n</ol>\n<h4>Example 1</h4>\n<pre>  <span class="fraction"><sup>4</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span> &times; <span class="fraction"><sup>3</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span> = <span class="fraction"><sup>(4 &times; 3)</sup>⁄<sub>(5 &times; 5)</sub></span> = <span class="fraction"><sup>12</sup>⁄<sub>25</sub></span> </pre>\n<h4>Example 2</h4>\n<pre>  <span class="fraction"><sup>4</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span> &times; <span class="fraction"><sup>3</sup>⁄<sub>2</sub></span> = <span class="fraction"><sup>(4 &times; 3)</sup>⁄<sub>(5 &times; 2)</sub></span> = <span class="fraction"><sup>12</sup>⁄<sub>10</sub></span> = <span class="fraction"><sup>6</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span> (Simplified) </pre>\n<h4>Example 3</h4>\n<p>Multiplying fractions with whole number.</p>\n<p>Please note that a whole number can also be considered as a fraction by considering it’s denominator as 1.</p>\n<pre>  <span class="fraction"><sup>4</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span> &times; 2 = <span class="fraction"><sup>(4 &times; 2)</sup>⁄<sub>(5 &times; 1)</sub></span> = <span class="fraction"><sup>8</sup>⁄<sub>5</sub></span> </pre>',fields:{slug:"/mathematics/multiplying-fractions/"},frontmatter:{title:"Multiplying Fractions"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/mathematics/multiplying-fractions/"}}}});
